This paper deals with the optimization of communication protocols in unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV)-aided backscatter communication (BackCom) networks. The paper focuses on maximizing the system throughput by jointly optimizing the time allocation, reflection coefficient, and UAV trajectory. This topic falls under the category of computer networks and communications (cs.NI) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves the optimization of UAV trajectory, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper includes simulation results, which may fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
